FBIS3-3824 "drchi057_a_94010" FBIS-CHI-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Ecuadoran President To Undergo Medical Tests in U.S. OW2403011594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0051 GMT 24 Mar 94 OW2403011594 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Quito, March 23 (XINHUA) -- President Sixto Duran-Ballen will undertake medical tests in the U.S. on his way back from a trip to Japan and China, according to Ecuadoran Government sources. Duran-Ballen will have a health check immediately after arriving in Washington tomorrow. He took a spinal surgery in February, 1993. The sources also said that Duran-Ballen will remain in the United States till next Monday for some private activities.
